This paper is primarily focused on image super-resolution using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also introduces a novel Spatial Feature Transform (SFT) layer, which involves learning affine transformation parameters for spatial-wise feature modulation, which could potentially fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also discusses the comparison of their proposed method with state-of-the-art super-resolution techniques, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) categories.
